\name{marpoly-package}
\alias{marpoly-package}
\alias{marpoly}
\docType{package}
\title{Mixed Causal-Noncausal Autoregressions and Polyspectral Estimation}
\description{
Tools for simulation, polyspectral analysis, estimation, root allocation ranking, and diagnostics for mixed causal-noncausal autoregressive models.
}
\details{
The package implements periodograms and spectral densities of orders 2, 3, and 4, MAR(r,s) simulation under stationarity restrictions, pseudo-causal AR order selection, frequency-domain minimum-distance estimation, residual extraction, and diagnostic plots.
}
\references{
Hecq, A. and Velasquez-Gaviria, D. (2025). Spectral estimation for mixed causal-noncausal autoregressive models. Econometric Reviews, 44(7), 939--962. DOI: 10.1080/07474938.2025.2465372.

Velasco, C. and Lobato, I. N. (2018). Frequency domain minimum distance inference for possibly noninvertible and noncausal ARMA models. The Annals of Statistics, 46(2), 555--579. DOI: 10.1214/17-AOS1560.
}
